  "texts": [
    "Our preregistered hypothesis (https://osf.io/t9rm6) was the GPT-4 would be evaluated as better than humans on 3 of four of the reappraisal measures: effectiveness, empathy and novelly but not specificity (similar to Study 1).",
    "We also had an exploratory hypothesis -that higher level of reappraisal by GPT would lead participants who received a reappraisal from GPT to more interested to continue the conversation compared to those who paired with a person.",
    "Validating the negativity of the vignettes.",
    "Participants were asked to estimate the negativity and positivity of the scenarios provided by their counterpart.",
    "This was done using two items one estimating the degree of negativity (1-not at all negative, 5-extremely negative) and positivity (1-not at all positive, 5 -extremely positive)."
